      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The inconsistency in your sourdough starter is likely due to the wild yeast and bacteria going through different phases of their life cycle, not just the temperature. When the starter is active, the yeast is rapidly consuming sugars, producing carbon dioxide, which causes the rise. If it stalls, it might be because the food source is temporarily depleted, or the microbial population is just entering a less vigorous phase before another feeding. You can try feeding it more frequently or using a slightly warmer spot, perhaps around 78°F, to give the colony a little extra boost.",
